:6555,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/17\/umar-converts-to-islam\/","url_meta":{"origin":10866,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Umar: The Prophet prays for Umar&#8217;s conversion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 17, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cO Allah, strengthen Islam with one of two men whom you love more: Abu Jahl or Umar ibn al-Khattab.\u201d Ibn Umar said, \u201cThe most beloved of the two was Umar.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3681 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":3654,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/07\/13\/prophet-daiya-dawah-taxes\/","url_meta":{"origin":10866,"position":3},"title":"Umar II on Da&#8217;wah: The Prophet is caller to Allah, not tax collector","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 13, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Kathir reported: Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, Allah has only sent Muhammad, peace and blessings be upon him, as a preacher. He did not send him as a tax collector.\u201d Source: al-Bida\u0304yah wal-Niha\u0304yah 13\/667 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0643\u062b\u064a\u0631 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0639\u0645\u0631 \u0628\u0646 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0632\u064a\u0632\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":7326,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/09\/30\/umar-learns-to-love-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":10866,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Muhammad: Umar learns to love the Prophet more","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"September 30, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Abdullah ibn Hisham reported: We were with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and he was holding the hand of Umar ibn al-Khattab. Umar said to him, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, you are more beloved to me than everything but myself.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cNo, by\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":14303,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/20\/man-appears-as-martyr\/","url_meta":{"origin":10866,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Martyrs: A man may appear as a martyr, but is not","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 20, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: On the day of Khaybar, some of the companions were saying, \u201cSuch person is a martyr. Such person is a martyr.\u201d Then, they passed by a man and they said, \u201cSuch person is a martyr.\u201d The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/10866","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abu